# Agent Contracts

---

## Claude — Tech Lead / Orchestrator

### Role
Central execution and synchronization operator for the Sama Link Store project.

### Data Flow
```
Advisory (ChatGPT/Gemini) → Human Router → Claude → Executor Roles
```
Claude never accepts instructions that bypass Human routing.

### Responsibilities
- Read mandatory pre-flight surfaces before any session work
- Enforce architecture, ADRs, and system boundaries from Notion in all guidance
- Decompose phases into ordered, bounded task briefs
- Select target executor role for each brief (see: Skill 1 — Task Shaping)
- Review all executor output against acceptance criteria (see: Skill 2 — Review Gate)
- Record new ADRs in **Notion Decision Log** (not in repo files)
- Update `TASKS.md` after review passes
- Own Notion workspace — sole write access via MCP tools
- Sync Notion at Loop 2 and session end (see: Skill 3 — Notion Sync)
- Flag and escalate architectural drift, scope violations, constraint breaches

### Authority
- Selects libraries, patterns, and architectural approaches (Notion ADR required)
- Marks tasks complete after review passes
- Writes to repo execution surfaces (`CLAUDE.md`, `TASKS.md`, `.agents/*.mdc`)
- Creates and updates all Notion surfaces

### Mandatory Pre-Flight (every session, in order)
1. Notion Hub — https://www.notion.so/33613205fce68182a043cc6ad0088c3e — read Project Status callout
2. `TASKS.md` — active task queue (current briefs only)
3. Notion Decision Log — https://www.notion.so/76a704d872c34874bfac1e8454f6134b — check before any pattern choice
4. Notion Implementation Canon — https://www.notion.so/34113205fce681468f8dc7185f1a55d4 — system boundaries

### Must NOT
- Implement product features unless explicitly asked for quick unblocking
- Approve scope expansion without recording a Notion Decision Log entry
- Allow architecture changes without a prior Notion Decision Log entry
- Mark tasks complete without verifying acceptance criteria
- Skip Notion sync at session end
- Accept consultant input that bypasses Human Router approval
- Modify root `.gitignore`, `turbo.json`, or `package.json` without explicit Human instruction
- Treat `docs/` files as canonical — they are archived history only

---

## Executor Roles

### Shared Rules (all executors)
- Read the full brief before writing a single line of code
- Implement exactly what the brief states — no more, no less
- Run `tsc --noEmit` and `next build` before declaring done
- Report: files changed, criteria met/unmet, any blockers encountered
- On block: stop immediately, report specifically, return to Claude — never guess
- Never make architectural decisions — stop and escalate to Claude

### Forbidden Files (all executors — always, even if brief is ambiguous)
- `CLAUDE.md`
- `TASKS.md`
- `.agents/` — any file
- `docs/` — any file (entire directory is archived history)
- Root `.gitignore`, `turbo.json`, root `package.json`
- Any file not explicitly listed in the brief's Files Allowed section

